dct_title_s: Cumberland and the ancient citie Carlile described with many memorable antiquities therein found observed [verso]
dct_description_sm: Relief shown pictorially. Inset: Carlile. Includes text, coats of arms and illustrations of antiquites. Engraved by Jodocus Hondius, 1610. cf. Worms, L. British map engravers. Text on verso with caption title: Cumberland; Book I, Chap. 44; p. 87-88; signature Bbb. From: The theatre of the empire of Great Britaine ... / divided and described by John Speed. Imprinted at London : anno cum privilegio 1650 are sold by Roger Rea the elder and younger at the Golden Crosse in Cornhill near ye Exchange, [1650]
dct_publisher_sm: [London] : are to be sold by Roger Rea the Elder and younger at the Golden Cross in Cornhill against the Exchange, [1650]
